The global beneficial insects market is projected to showcase significant growth by the year 2028. Beneficial insects play a crucial role in agriculture by providing natural pest control, pollination services, and overall ecosystem balance. The market is segmented by type, application, and region. Predatory insects, parasitic insects, and pollinator insects are the key types included in the market segmentation. Based on application, the market is categorized into crop protection, horticulture, forestry, greenhouse ornamental plants, and landscaping. Geographically, the market is analyzed across North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa.

